    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">A warrior is fighting a slime boss. The health of the slime boss is <var>H</var>. <br><br>On each turn, the warrior can attack a slime. When a slime is attacked, the following happens:<br>- If the slime's health is <const>1</const>, it disappears.<br>- If the slime's health is <strong>X</strong>, which is greater than <const>1</const>, it splits into two slimes with health <strong>X/2</strong>, rounded down.<br><br>The warrior wins when all the slimes have disappeared. Find the number of attacks they need to use before winning.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> An integer <var>H</var>: the initial health of the slime boss.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> The number of attacks the warrior needs to use before winning.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; <var>H</var> &le; 10⁶</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">3</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">3</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
